Guo Ailun (born November 14, 1993 in Liaoning) is a Chinese professional basketball player. He currently plays for the Liaoning Dinosaurs of the Chinese Basketball Association.[1] He is also a member of the Chinese national basketball team Guo is a member of the Chinese junior national basketball team, and captained the team at the FIBA Under-17 World Championship 2010.[2] He averaged a tournament-high 22.4 points per game for the seventh placed Chinese team.[3] Following this successful performance, he was a surprise choice to the Chinese senior team at the 2010 FIBA World Championship in Turkey. At 16 years of age, Guo was by far the youngest player in the tournament. 
